Step 1: Identify Quick Assets. Quick assets exclude inventory. From the balance sheet (End_amount):

• Cash on Hand: 4,058,544.03  
• Bank Deposits: 3,079,000.00  
• Interest Receivable: 13,279.60  
• Accounts Receivable: 2,984,071.72  

Step 2: Sum the quick assets.  
Total Quick Assets = 4,058,544.03 + 3,079,000.00 + 13,279.60 + 2,984,071.72  
  = 10,134,895.35

Step 3: Identify Total Current Liabilities (End_amount):  
Total Current Liabilities = 624,988.48

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio  
Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
  = 10,134,895.35 / 624,988.48  
  ≈ 16.22

Thus, the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 16.22.
